Diagnosis.
Male (
Fig. 1
). Body black or bluish black with metallic luster. Frons without orbital spots (
Fig. 2
), but velvety black parafacial spot present below level of antenna (
Fig. 3
). Frons with pair of posterior orbital setae (
Fig. 2
). Antennal scape yellowish to pale brown, paler than blackish brown pedicel and flagellum (
Fig. 3
). One pair of apical scutellar setae present. Femur yellow, the rest legs blackish brown (
Fig. 1
). Wing infumated, without spots, sometimes darker in distal portion. Female similar to male in external characters except terminalia.

Male terminalia: sternum 5 divided into two triangular sclerites (
Fig. 4
). Cerci with tubercle protuberance subapically (
Fig. 5
). Surstylus oval in caudal view (
Fig. 6
). Hypandrium tapering apically (
Fig. 7–8
). Aedeagal apodeme about as long as ejaculatory apodeme but dilated distally (
Fig. 9
).
